HEADWORD: Nearctic
<hw>Ne*arc"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Neo</ets> +
<ets>arctic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a region of the
earth's surface including all of temperate and arctic North America and
Greenland. In the geographical distribution of animals, this region is
marked off as the habitat certain species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

